                                      srv

Serve the contents of a given directory. I like it when I'm working on one off
HTML files.

INSTALLATION

* Make sure you have go setup properly.
* Then run "go get github.com/bplaxco/srv"
* Finally run "go install github.com/bplaxco/srv"

USAGE

-b=""      Bind to an address
-f="./"    Set the folder
-p="1337"  Set the port
